# Code Conventions

## Components
- Functional components ONLY — no class components
- Props interface naming: `ComponentNameProps`
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx` next to component
- Colocated styles: `ComponentName.scss` next to component

## TypeScript
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- Explicit return types for exported functions
- Use union types and discriminated unions for element types
- Prefer `ExcalidrawElement` union type from `packages/element/src/types.ts`

## File Naming
- PascalCase for React components: `ColorPicker.tsx`
- camelCase for utilities and hooks: `useHistory.ts`, `restore.ts`
- SCSS files colocated with components: `ColorPicker.scss`

## Imports
- Use package aliases: `@excalidraw/common`, `@excalidraw/math`, `@excalidraw/element`
- DO NOT use relative paths crossing package boundaries (e.g., `../../packages/math/`)
- Use `nanoid()` for ID generation (already a dependency)

## Error Handling
- Use custom error classes from `packages/excalidraw/errors.ts`
- CanvasError for rendering issues, AbortError for cancellations
- Never swallow errors silently — log or rethrow

## How to verify
- No `class extends React.Component` in new code
- No `any` type annotations in new code
- All new components have PascalCase filenames
- No cross-package relative imports (grep for `../../packages/`)
